Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of cases of enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ infection has risen to 14 with 4 of the 11 children developing HUS (hemolytic-uremic syndrome). It is not stated whether the organism is serotype O157:H7 or one of the other serotypes that produce Shiga toxin. Although the posting states that bacterial levels in the water were above "safe" limits, the results are likely reflective of an overall coliform level not of Shiga toxin producing _E. coli_ specifically, but does reflect fecal contamination. - Mod.LL

The state of California can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5240983,62262. Nevada county in central California can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/california-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
